article.description: — Evan Taylor scored 13 points and his layup with 10 seconds left carried Lehigh past Navy 63-62 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Taylor's late layup sends Lehigh past Navy 63-62
article.linkText: Taylor's late layup sends Lehigh past Navy 63-62
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Evan Taylor scored 13 points and his layup with 10 seconds left carried Lehigh past Navy 63-62 on Wednesday. Navy's Sean Yoder missed a 3-pointer as time expired to end it. Nic Lynch scored 18 points for Lehigh (9-14, 7-4 Patriot League). Greg Summers had 16 points and Tyler Nelson 10 for the Midshipmen (14-8, 7-4). John Carter Jr., the Midshipmen's leading scorer coming into the matchup at 13 points per game, was just 2-for-10 shooting. Lehigh also defeated Navy 69-61 on Jan. 19. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
